{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s16SendableMetatypeP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItem","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSCheckboxItem"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Controls"]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Layouts","anchor":"Layouts"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component can be rendered as two different layouts:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"default","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": the component has a leading indicator, a label and optional helper texts, and an optional trailing decorative icon"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"reversed"}]},{"type":"text","text":": like the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default"}]},{"type":"text","text":" layout but with a trailing checkbox indicator and a leading optional image"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Indicator states","anchor":"Indicator-states"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The checkbox indicator has three available states:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"selected","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": the checkbox is filled with a tick, the user has made the action to select the checkbox"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"unselected"}]},{"text":": the checkbox is empty, does not contain a tick, the user has made the action to unselect or did not select yet the checkbox","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you are looking for a checkbox component with three states, use instead "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Particular cases","anchor":"Particular-cases"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItem"},{"type":"text","text":" can be related to an error situation, for example troubles for a formular."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A dedicated look and feel is implemented for that if the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isError"},{"type":"text","text":" flag is risen."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In that case if the component displayed an icon, this icon will be replaced automatically by an error icon."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In addition, the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItem","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" can be in read only mode, i.e. the user cannot interact with the component yet but this component must not be considered"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as disabled."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component does not follow the right-to-left (RTL) \/ left-to-right (LTR) mode returned by the system as it could have some meaning"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to have for example the indicator in trailing position for LTR mode and vice versa."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However, if the component has an icon in leading position (RTL mode) or in trailing position (LTR), the content of the icon is never changed."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It could lead to a loss of meaning or semantics in the icon. Thus a specific flag can be used to flip the icon content whatever the layout direction is."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It prevents the user do implement its own rules to flip or not image."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Accessibility considerations","anchor":"Accessibility-considerations"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Voice Over","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" will use several elements to describe the component: if component disabled \/ read only, if error context, the label and helper texts and a custom checkbox trait.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"No accessibility identifier is defined in OUDSThemesContract side as this value remains in the users hands.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Forbidden by design","anchor":"Forbidden-by-design"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a read only component.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a disabled component.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The design system does not allow to have both a read only and a disabled component.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Code samples","anchor":"Code-samples"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ Supposing we have an unselected checkbox","    @Published var isOn: Bool = false","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItem(isOn: $isOn, label: \"Hello world\")","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label, but in read only mode (user cannot interact yet, but not disabled).","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItem(isOn: $isOn, label: \"Hello world\", isReadOnly: true)","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label, and an helper text.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItem(isOn: $isOn, label: \"Bazinga!\", helper: \"Doll-Dagga Buzz-Buzz Ziggety-Zag\")","","    \/\/ A trailing checkbox with a label, an helper text and an icon.","    \/\/ The reversed layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItem(isOn: $isOn,","                     label: \"We live in a fabled world\",","                     helper: \"Of dreaming boys and wide-eyed girls\",","                     isReversed: true,","                     icon: Image(decorative: \"ic_heart\"))","","    \/\/ If on error, add an error message can help user to understand error context","    OUDSCheckboxItem(isOn: $isOn,","                     label: \"We live in a fabled world\",","                     isError: true,","                     errorText: \"Something wrong\",","                     hasDivider: true)","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label, but disabled.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItem(isOn: $isOn, label: \"Hello world\")","        .disabled(true)","","    \/\/ Never disable a read only or an error-related checkbox as it will crash","    \/\/ This is forbidden by design!","    OUDSCheckboxItem(isOn: $isOn, label: \"Hello world\", isError: true).disabled(true) \/\/ fatal error","    OUDSCheckboxItem(isOn: $isOn, label: \"Hello world\", isReadyOnly: true).disabled(true) \/\/ fatal error"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you want to manage the RTL mode quite easily and switch your layouts (flip image, indicator in RTL leading i.e. in the right):","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    @Environment(\\.layoutDirection) var layoutDirection","","    OUDSCheckboxItem(isOn: $selection,","                     labelText: \"Cocorico !\",","                     icon: Image(systemName: \"figure.handball\"),","                     flipIcon: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft,","                     isInversed: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft)"]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Suggestions","anchor":"Suggestions"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"According to the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/unified-design-system.orange.com\/472794e18\/p\/23f1c1-checkbox\/b\/6578e5\/t\/3dd013a529","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the checkbox by default must be used in unselected state.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Design documentation","anchor":"Design-documentation"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/unified-design-system.orange.com\/472794e18\/p\/23f1c1-checkbox","isActive":true}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Themes rendering","anchor":"Themes-rendering"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Orange","anchor":"Orange"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_checkboxItem_Orange"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Orange Business Tools","anchor":"Orange-Business-Tools"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_checkboxItem_OrangeBusinessTools","type":"image"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Sosh","anchor":"Sosh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_checkboxItem_Sosh","type":"image"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Wireframe","anchor":"Wireframe"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_checkboxItem_Wireframe"}]},{"type":"aside","name":"Version","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"2.3.0 (Figma component design version)","type":"text"}]}],"style":"note"},{"type":"aside","name":"Since","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0.12.0"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note"}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:14OUDSComponents16OUDSCheckboxItemV","roleHeading":"Structure","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"struct","modules":[{"name":"Components"}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSCheckboxItem","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OUDSCheckboxItem","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"OUDSCheckboxItem"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItem"},{"text":" proposes layouts to add in your views some checkboxes components with labels and icons.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If you want to use a checkbox with only an indicator prefer instead ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckbox"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItem\/init(isOn:label:helper:icon:flipIcon:isReversed:isError:errorText:isReadOnly:hasDivider:action:)"],"anchor":"Initializers"},{"generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItem\/body"],"anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"generated":true,"title":"Default Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponent